metadata.name: Stitched #74
metadata.description:
You are the product of countless tiny decisions taken over the course of your life. Stitched is an attempt to visualize one’s current self as a product of the myriad forking paths available to us. It is best appreciated in animated format: the latent structure unfolds in time; the past gradually fades away, tinted and obscure. 

Past decisions and missed opportunities leave a trail on the present. Psychology affects what you explore: drive controls how frequent one changes direction; indecisive mints explore many loose ends; balanced mints match complementary colours.

Stitched is adaptive to arbitrary screen resolution and aspect ratio, and best appreciated at high resolution. It initially renders with a large step size in time; pause and unpause to watch it unfold more gradually.

controls:

mouse click or space bar: pause / unpause / reset animation
s: save current frame

Inspired by The Garden of Forking Paths by Borges and stylistically by French and Russian Impressionists, and Autoglyphs by Larva Labs.

metadata.name: Omega Point #150
metadata.description:
In the collapsing universe approaching singularity, the last remaining cybernetic organisms encounter the state of infinite knowledge, information, and computational resources.
Although the living creatures in the Omega Point are destined for imminent destruction, they experience infinite life.

----

Live mode controls:
'r' - change resolution
's' - save PNG
'space' - improve image quality
'f' - increase rendering speed

The image quality gradually improves over time, up to a certain level. To reach the maximum quality, press 'space'.
The rendering speed is reduced by default - press 'f' for the maximum speed.

Rendering may be GPU intensive.
Requires WebGL2.

metadata.name: Hexaëder #113
metadata.description:
Hexaëder (cube) is a research into abstraction and a search for a balance between simplification and visual complexity.

No matter how simple and unambiguous things appear to be, in reality they are often more complex. Enjoy the simple, explore the complex.

Hexaeder has a wide variety of possible outcomes. I have put together 10 different color palettes; the number of cubes ranges from 10 to 401 (18 different grids); each cell can have 4 different background patterns; each cube can be filled in 4 distinct ways; there are 5 line colors and 16 different "cube figures"; the vignette can be black or be the color of the palette, and there are several "texture settings". This results in over 1.8 million possibilities.

For more information see: https://www.behance.net/gallery/131114761/Hexaeder-Flattened-cubes

metadata.name: Atoms' Gaze #50
metadata.description:
How the lives of many affect the whole.

A holistic exploration of the growth of crystalline structures. Discovering the complexity of natural forms built from the simple rules of a deterministic system. What choice do individuals have but to be part of the story?

As microscopic particles interact and coalesce they form the macrocosm. The path they take however, is only known once it is complete. Along the way they may encounter many or none at all; each instance defining its past and future. The only knowns are that this will be the only path they take and that it'll always end.

Enjoy watching the structures form. Due to the nature of the system it may take some time to complete. Once it's fully rendered you can download a full resolution image by ***double clicking/tapping***

Features include: palette, foreground and background structures, particle rules, number of particles, colour displacement and noise.

Created on Chrome desktop 100.0 on 2022-04-16. Results on other browsers/devices may vary.

metadata.name: Window gratings #83
metadata.description:
Window gratings were once a ubiquitous sight in Taiwan. Starting around the 1950s, homeowners began installing stylized metal barriers in front of their windows to keep out thieves.

The artwork focused on window gratings and add some fantastic colors & materials.
Wait for seconds and you'll see time flies.

100,000 possible buildings & floors combinations  
20 different color palette + 20 monotone (20%)
9 unique Window grating styles
6 door styles
4 roof and 4 fence styles
3 room styles

[keyboard] Press 's' to save PNG in original size
